## HIGH — Email-verified waitlist registration backend

### What's wrong
No waitlist system exists. Users can't sign up for early access with email verification.

### What to build

#### 1. Migration `026_waitlist` in `database.ts`

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS waitlist_entries (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  verified BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  verified_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  ip_address TEXT,
  user_agent TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_waitlist_email ON waitlist_entries(email);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS email_verification_tokens (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT NOT NULL,
  token TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
  used BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_email_verif_token ON email_verification_tokens(token);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_email_verif_email ON email_verification_tokens(email);
```

Use existing migration pattern:
```typescript
if (!(await this.isMigrationApplied('026_waitlist'))) {
  await pool.query(`...SQL above...`);
  await this.recordMigration('026_waitlist');
}
```

#### 2. Email validation utility — `backend/.../src/utils/email-validation.ts`

Do basic programmatic checks BEFORE sending any email:

```typescript
export interface EmailValidationResult {
  valid: boolean;
  reason?: string; // 'invalid_format' | 'no_mx_records' | 'disposable_domain'
}

export async function validateEmail(email: string): Promise<EmailValidationResult>
```

**3 checks (in order, short-circuit on failure):**

1. **Format check** — Use a robust regex or `validator.isEmail()` (express-validator's `isEmail` already used in auth.ts). Check: non-empty, has @, domain part has dot, no spaces, max 254 chars.

2. **MX record check** — `dns.promises.resolveMx(domain)` — reject if no MX records found. Wrap in try/catch, treat DNS errors as soft-fail (allow through with warning log).

3. **Disposable domain blocklist** — Hardcoded array of ~50 common disposable email domains:
```typescript
const DISPOSABLE_DOMAINS = [
  'mailinator.com', 'guerrillamail.com', 'tempmail.com', 'throwaway.email',
  'yopmail.com', 'sharklasers.com', 'guerrillamail.info', 'grr.la',
  'guerrillamail.net', 'guerrillamail.org', 'guerrillamail.de',
  'trbvm.com', 'dispostable.com', 'temp-mail.org', 'fakeinbox.com',
  'mailnesia.com', 'maildrop.cc', 'discard.email', 'trashmail.com',
  'trashmail.me', 'trashmail.net', 'trashmail.org', 'harakirimail.com',
  'objectmail.com', 'proxymail.eu', 'rcpt.at', 'trash-mail.at',
  'trashmail.at', 'trashmail.io', 'wegwerfmail.de', 'wegwerfmail.net',
  'wegwerfmail.org', 'getairmail.com', 'mailcatch.com', 'mytemp.email',
  'mohmal.com', 'burner.kiwi', 'tempail.com', 'getnada.com',
  'mintemail.com', '10minutemail.com', 'mailnator.com', 'spamgourmet.com',
  'maildrop.cc', 'guerrillamailblock.com', 'grr.la', 'spam4.me',
];
```
Extract domain from email, check against list.

#### 3. Email service — `backend/.../src/services/email.ts`

```typescript
import nodemailer from 'nodemailer';

const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({
  service: 'gmail',
  auth: {
    user: process.env.EMAIL_USER,
    pass: process.env.EMAIL_APP_PASSWORD,  // Gmail App Password (not regular password)
  },
});

export async function sendVerificationEmail(to: string, token: string): Promise<void> {
  const verifyUrl = `${process.env.APP_URL || 'http://localhost:3000'}/waitlist/verify?token=${token}`;

  await transporter.sendMail({
    from: `"CookQuest" <${process.env.EMAIL_USER}>`,
    to,
    subject: 'Verify your email — CookQuest Waitlist',
    html: `
      <div style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px;">
        <h2 style="color: #f59e0b;">Welcome to CookQuest!</h2>
        <p>Thanks for signing up for the waitlist. Click below to verify your email:</p>
        <a href="${verifyUrl}" style="display: inline-block; padding: 12px 24px; background: #f59e0b; color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: bold;">Verify Email</a>
        <p style="margin-top: 16px; color: #666; font-size: 14px;">This link expires in 24 hours.</p>
        <p style="color: #999; font-size: 12px;">If you didn't sign up, ignore this email.</p>
      </div>
    `,
  });
}
```

**Env vars needed:** `EMAIL_USER`, `EMAIL_APP_PASSWORD`, `APP_URL`

#### 4. API routes — `backend/.../src/routes/waitlist.ts`

**POST /api/v1/waitlist/signup**
```typescript
// Body: { email: string }
// Flow:
//   1. Validate with express-validator (isEmail, normalizeEmail)
//   2. Run validateEmail() — format, MX, disposable checks
//   3. Check if email already verified in waitlist_entries → 409 'Already on waitlist'
//   4. Generate crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex') token
//   5. Delete any existing unused tokens for this email (prevent buildup)
//   6. INSERT into email_verification_tokens (email, token, expires_at = NOW() + 24h)
//   7. UPSERT into waitlist_entries (email, ip, user_agent) — unverified
//   8. Call sendVerificationEmail(email, token)
//   9. Return { success: true, message: 'Verification email sent. Check your inbox.' }
// Rate limit: 3 per email per hour, 10 per IP per hour
// Error handling: if email send fails, still return success (don't leak SMTP errors)
```

**GET /api/v1/waitlist/verify**
```typescript
// Query: ?token=xxx
// Flow:
//   1. Look up token in email_verification_tokens WHERE used = false AND expires_at > NOW()
//   2. If not found → redirect to /waitlist/verify?status=invalid
//   3. Mark token as used
//   4. UPDATE waitlist_entries SET verified = true, verified_at = NOW() WHERE email = token.email
//   5. Redirect to /waitlist/verify?status=success
// This is a GET because users click a link in their email
```

**Register in index.ts:**
```typescript
import { waitlistRoutes } from './waitlist'
// Public route (no auth required)
app.use(`${apiPrefix}/waitlist`, waitlistRoutes)
```

#### 5. DB helpers in `database.ts`

```typescript
static async getWaitlistEntry(email: string): Promise<WaitlistEntry | null>
static async upsertWaitlistEntry(email: string, ip?: string, userAgent?: string): Promise<void>
static async verifyWaitlistEntry(email: string): Promise<void>
static async createVerificationToken(email: string, token: string, expiresAt: Date): Promise<void>
static async getVerificationToken(token: string): Promise<VerificationToken | null>
static async markTokenUsed(token: string): Promise<void>
static async deleteUnusedTokensForEmail(email: string): Promise<void>
static async getRecentSignupCount(email: string, windowMinutes: number): Promise<number>
```

#### 6. Install nodemailer

```bash
cd backend/node-services/api-server && npm install nodemailer && npm install -D @types/nodemailer
```

### Subtasks
1. Install nodemailer + @types/nodemailer
2. Add migration 026 to database.ts initializeDatabase()
3. Add DB helper methods for waitlist + tokens
4. Create utils/email-validation.ts with 3-check validation
5. Create services/email.ts with Gmail SMTP transport
6. Create routes/waitlist.ts with POST /signup and GET /verify
7. Register waitlist routes in index.ts
8. Add rate limiting to signup route
9. Verify build passes

### Depends on
none

### Acceptance criteria
- Given valid email, when POST /waitlist/signup, then verification email sent and 200 returned
- Given disposable email (mailinator.com), when POST /signup, then 400 with 'Disposable email addresses are not allowed'
- Given email with no MX records, when POST /signup, then 400 with 'Email domain does not accept mail'
- Given valid token, when GET /waitlist/verify?token=xxx, then entry marked verified and redirect to success
- Given expired/used token, when GET /verify, then redirect to error page
- Given already-verified email, when POST /signup again, then 409 'Already on waitlist'
- All SQL uses $N placeholders (PostgreSQL)
- Rate limited: 3 per email/hour, 10 per IP/hour

